deleted, so past data is still available on the metrics dashboard.

entry.title: [Autofill] Also TriggerReparse() in frames without seen form
entry.content:
FormForest::UpdateTreeOfRendererForm() triggers a reparse in the parent

frame if the parent form isn't known yet. This happens in the following

cases:

- The parent form has not (yet) been processed by

UpdateTreeOfRendererForm().

- The frame token has changed since the parent form has been extracted

and processed by UpdateTreeOfRendererForm().



Before this CL, TriggerReparse() was only done in frames for which

some form had been seen already. That is, TriggerReparse() was not

called

- in parent documents that are documents, or

- if FormsSeen() had not been executed for the parent frame, yet.



This CL triggers the reparse in the parent frame independent of whether

a form has been seen in it.



The motivation is just simplicity, especially once crrev.com/c/4499288

has removed //content dependencies from FormForest.



This comes at the cost of additional AutofillAgent::ProcessForms() calls

in the two cases mentioned above. A followup CL will address the

throttling of ProcessForms() to reduce duplicate work in the renderer.



Bug: 1187842, 1443645

entry.title: [v8][wasm] Increase the limit on sync compilation on the main thread
entry.content:
With the introduction of the baseline compiler Liftoff and lazy

compilation, the execution time of synchronous WebAssembly compilation

has decreased significantly. Additionally hardware has improved since

the definition of the original limit of 4KB. Therefore this CL

increases the limit to 8MB.



The limit was determined by performance measurements on a Google

Pixel 1, which we considered as a representative low-end phone. This

phone was able to compile an 8MB module in less than 200ms, which is

the threshold for good responsiveness in the metric "interaction to

next paint" defined by Google's Core Web Vitals.

entry.title: [rust] Fix Fuchsia -pie warning.
entry.content:
When linking executables, rustc builds a command line for our chosen

linker (clang++). In that command line it adds -pie, which makes no

difference on the Fuchsia platform and clang++ complains about it.

As warnings are fatal, this prevents Rust from linking executables on

the Fuchsia platform. Suppress those warnings.



Alternative solution considered: on the Fuchsia platform, instruct rustc

to use lld as the linker instead of clang++. This is apparently what is

done on the Fuchsia OS builds. However, Chromium's many gn templates

assemble complex sets of clang++ ldflags across multiple platforms and

sanitizer configurations - it would be disruptive to switch to using a

different linker for just some builds.



Alternative solution considered: add this warning suppression in

//build/rust/rustc_wrapper.py. This would have the advantage that it

would only apply to binaries linked by rustc, whereas the current

arrangement will unfortunately suppress this warning even for binaries

linked by clang++ (e.g. Chromium itself). On balance, though, it seems

nicer to use gn's configuration mechanism than to hard code something in

a python script.

entry.title: FSA: Remove disabling of BFCache on use of any local file
entry.content:
BFCache is currently disabled when using the File System Access API to

interact with _any_ local files in any way. This was added back in

https://crrev.com/c/1837813 due to its use of

RenderFrameHost::IsCurrent, which at the time returned true

for iframes



However, the behavior of RenderFrameHost::IsCurrent was changed in

https://crrev.com/c/2060374 such that it's no longer necessary to

disable BFCache in this specific case.

See https://crbug.com/1259861 for more details.



Note that BFCache is still disabled when permission to a file is

requested from the File System Access API.

This behavior was added in https://crrev.com/c/3217485 and requires

further work to address



Bug: 1241174, 1259861

entry.title: Implement SharedDictionary{Manager/Storage}OnDisk
entry.content:
This CL implements SharedDictionaryManagernDisk and

SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk. SharedDictionaryManagerOnDisk holds a

SharedDictionaryDiskCache and a SQLitePersistentSharedDictionaryStore.



A SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk is created for the given

net::SharedDictionaryStorageIsolationKey to manage the dictionaries.

It loads the all dictionary information for the

net::SharedDictionaryStorageIsolationKey from the

SQLitePersistentSharedDictionaryStore, and stores the information to

`dictionary_info_map_`.



When GetDictionary() is called, SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk returns a

SharedDictionary which loads the dictionary binary from the

SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk.



When CreateWriter() is called, SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk returns a

SharedDictionaryWriterOnDisk which writes the dictionary binary into the

SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk. When the writer finishes writing the

binary, SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk::OnDictionaryWrittenInDiskCache()

is called. And the SharedDictionaryStorageOnDisk will write the

dictionary metadata into SQLitePersistentSharedDictionaryStore.



Low-Coverage-Reason: This line only runs on Android.
